INTRODUCTION 
Pregnancy is a unique and complex physiological process 
during which the expectant mother undergoes numerous 
changes to support the developing foetus. Nutrition in 
pregnancy plays a vital role in ensuring the health and 
well-being of both the expectant mother and the 
developing foetus. 
Adequate intake of key nutrients, along with proper 
management of nutritional challenges, can contribute to
